  "instructions": [
    "Heat a dash of oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook for 5 minutes until softened.",
    "Add the parsnips and cook for a further 5 minutes.",
    "Add the turkey mince and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until browned.",
    "Add the garlic, cabbage, flour, ale, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the crumbled cheddar cheese until melted and well combined.",
    "Spoon the mixture into the stone bowls and serve hot, garnished with a sprig of fresh parsley."
